snippet: The Libyan government has rebuffed the Obama administration’s efforts to arrest suspects in the killings of an American ambassador and three other Americans.
abstract: Fledgling Libyan government has rebuffed the Obama administration's efforts to arrest suspects indicted for their roles in the attacks in Benghazi that killed the United States ambassador to Libya and three other Americans.

byline.original: By MICHAEL S. SCHMIDT and ERIC SCHMITT

lead_paragraph: The Libyan government has rebuffed the Obama administration’s efforts to arrest suspects in the killings of an American ambassador and three other Americans.

headline.main: Libya Thwarts Arrests in Benghazi Attack
